      <section eId="sec_CHC-1426">
        <num>CHC 1426</num>
        <heading>1426. Â Right to hearing</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1426__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Prior to or during confinement under the provisions of this Title, any minor or his attorney shall have the right to demand a judicial hearing to determine if probable cause exists for his continued confinement under an emergency certificate.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1426__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The hearing shall be held within five days of the filing of the petition.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1426__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Pending the decision of the court, the minor patient shall remain confined unless the court orders release or a less restrictive status.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72922</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
